Ukrainian sugar production will fall
about 23 percent this year to 1.8 million metric tons, Interfax-
Ukraine reported.  Sugar-beet planting in the country dropped to 480,000
hectares (1.2 million acres), compared with 540,000 hectares in
2011, the news agency said today. It cited Oleksandr Demydov,
